{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-plugin-manifest.json",
  "name": "ultraprompt",
  "version": "${version}",
  "description": "Ultraprompt V${version_mm} cognitive control-plane plugin for Claude Code and Codex: ${catalog.skills} skills, ${catalog.agents} agents, ${catalog.mcp_tools} MCP tools, ${catalog.commands} commands, typed local memory, safe dream jobs, governed learning, workflow pathfinding, capability graph, live Mission Control dashboard, evidence-led release gates, dual-runtime install. V${version_mm} completes the release-integrity pass: a single VERSION file is the source of truth for every version site; render-manifest --check now fails CI on any version drift (CHANGELOG, the Codex manifest, and the rendered manifests must all agree); the SubagentStart hook is single-sourced so POSIX and Windows cannot diverge; and README plus manifest catalog counts render from one template so they cannot go stale.",
